    "slug": "12-early-adopters-of-the-ngo-and-ong-domains",
    "link": "https://www.nptechforgood.com/2015/12/13/12-early-adopters-of-the-ngo-and-ong-domains/",
    "title": {
      "rendered": "12 Early Adopters of the .NGO and .ONG Domains"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Early-Adopter-NGOs-ONGs-Domains-Facebook.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-18818\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Early-Adopter-NGOs-ONGs-Domains-Facebook-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"Early Adopter NGOs ONGs Domains Facebook\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Early-Adopter-NGOs-ONGs-Domains-Facebook.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Early-Adopter-NGOs-ONGs-Domains-Facebook.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Early-Adopter-NGOs-ONGs-Domains-Facebook.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Early-Adopter-NGOs-ONGs-Domains-Facebook.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Early-Adopter-NGOs-ONGs-Domains-Facebook.jpg?w=800&amp;ssl=1 800w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a>Unlike the .ORG domain which can be registered by any individual or brand (but mostly registered by nonprofits and socially conscious for-profits), the <strong><a href=\"https://www.ongood.ngo/portal/registrars\" target=\"_blank\">new .NGO and .ONG domains</a></strong> can only be registered by nonprofits, charities, NGOs (non-governmental organizations), and ONGs (non-governmental organizations in a <strong><a href=\"http://globalngo.org/world-maps-ngo-and-ong-usage-around-the-globe/\" target=\"_blank\">romance-based language</a></strong>). <em>Think about that for a second or two</em>. When your online donors and advocates see that your nonprofit uses .NGO or .ONG for your website URL and email addresses, there will be no doubt in their minds that your nonprofit is legal <strong><em>because your nonprofit must complete a\u00a0<a href=\"https://www.flickr.com/photos/nonprofitorgs/19470129505/in/album-72157655116691039/\" target=\"_blank\">validation process</a>\u00a0via <a href=\"https://www.ongood.ngo/portal/\" target=\"_blank\">OnGood</a>\u00a0to be able to use the domain</em>s</strong>. In an online world where anyone or any brand can launch online fundraising campaign through third-party crowdfunding sites (such as <a href=\"https://www.gofundme.com/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>GoFundMe</strong></a> and <strong><a href=\"http://www.indiegogo.com\" target=\"_blank\">Indiegogo</a></strong>), it will become increasingly important to communicate to online donors and\u00a0advocates that your nonprofit is legal, valid, and an online brand to be trusted.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">That said, below is a list of early adopters using the new .NGO and .ONG domains. Current growth is occurring in parts of the world where &#8220;NGO&#8221; and &#8220;ONG&#8221; are commonly used terms and in regions where &#8220;nonprofit&#8221; and &#8220;charity&#8221; are more common, many nonprofits and charities are purchasing the domains (they are sold as a bundle) and having them forward to their .ORG website(s).</p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">1. Australian Wildlife Conservancy\u00a0\u25cf\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.australianwildlife.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\">australianwildlife.ngo<br />\n</a>?\u00a0Australia</h2>\n<p><strong>Mission:</strong> To establish wildlife sanctuaries by acquiring land and through partnerships with landholders.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.australianwildlife.ngo\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18789\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Australian-Wildlife-Conservancy.png?resize=600%2C282\" alt=\"Australian Wildlife Conservancy\" width=\"600\" height=\"282\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Australian-Wildlife-Conservancy.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Australian-Wildlife-Conservancy.png?resize=300%2C141&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">2. Educate Girls\u00a0\u25cf<span lang=\"en\"> <a href=\"http://www.educategirls.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\">educategirls.ngo<br />\n</a></span>?\u00a0India</h2>\n<p><strong>Mission:</strong> To improve access and quality of education for 4 million children\u00a0living in underserved communities in India.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://educategirls.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18790\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Educate-Girls.png?resize=600%2C259\" alt=\"Educate Girls\" width=\"600\" height=\"259\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Educate-Girls.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Educate-Girls.png?resize=300%2C130&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">3. Funda\u00e7\u00e3o Roberto Marinho \u25cf<span lang=\"en\"> <a href=\"http://www.frm.ong\" target=\"_blank\">frm.ong</a><a href=\"http://www.aida.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\"><br />\n</a></span>?\u00a0Brazil</h2>\n<p><strong>Mission:</strong> To\u00a0promote the right to education and to preserve the environment and cultural heritage of Brazil.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.frm.ong\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18787\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/FRM.png?resize=600%2C282\" alt=\"FRM\" width=\"600\" height=\"282\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/FRM.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/FRM.png?resize=300%2C141&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>4.\u00a0Grassroots Pakistan\u00a0\u25cf\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.grassrootspakistan.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\">grassrootspakistan.ngo<br />\n</a>?\u00a0Pakistan</h2>\n<p><strong>Mission:\u00a0</strong>To help eradicate extreme poverty through community development projects in\u00a0urban sanitation, water filtration, health, alternative energy, and economic empowerment.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.grassrootspakistan.ngo\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18797\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Grassroots-Pakistan.png?resize=600%2C273\" alt=\"Grassroots Pakistan\" width=\"600\" height=\"273\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Grassroots-Pakistan.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Grassroots-Pakistan.png?resize=300%2C137&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>5. Kijani \u25cf\u00a0<a href=\"http://kijani.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\">kijani.ngo<br />\n</a>?\u00a0Kenya</h2>\n<p><strong>Mission:</strong> To restore Kenyan highland forests and elevate the discussion on sustainability.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://kijani.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18771\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Kijani.png?resize=600%2C273\" alt=\"Kijani\" width=\"600\" height=\"273\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Kijani.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Kijani.png?resize=300%2C137&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>6. International Corporate Accountability Roundtable\u00a0\u25cf\u00a0<a href=\"http://icar.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\">icar.ngo<br />\n</a>?\u00a0United States</h2>\n<p><strong>Mission:</strong> To ensure corporations respect human rights in their global operations.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://icar.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18799\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/ICAR.png?resize=600%2C278\" alt=\"ICAR\" width=\"600\" height=\"278\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/ICAR.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/ICAR.png?resize=300%2C139&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>7. Kopernik\u00a0\u25cf\u00a0<a href=\"https://www.kopernik.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\">kopernik.ngo<br />\n</a>?\u00a0Indonesia</h2>\n<p><strong>Mission:</strong> To fund social entrepreneurs in the developing world through crowdfunding.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.kopernik.ngo\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18803\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Kopernik.png?resize=600%2C280\" alt=\"Kopernik\" width=\"600\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Kopernik.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Kopernik.png?resize=300%2C140&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2>8. International Society of Street Papers\u00a0\u25cf <a href=\"http://insp.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\">insp.ngo</a><br />\n?\u00a0Scotland</h2>\n<p><strong>Mission:</strong> To support 113 street paper enterprises in 34 countries in order to combat urban poverty.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://insp.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18773\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/INSP-Street-Papers.png?resize=600%2C270\" alt=\"INSP Street Papers\" width=\"600\" height=\"270\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/INSP-Street-Papers.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/INSP-Street-Papers.png?resize=300%2C135&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">9. Naves de Esperanza\u00a0\u25cf\u00a0<a href=\"https://www.nde.ong/\" target=\"_blank\">nde.ong<br />\n</a>?\u00a0Spain</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>Mission:</strong> To provide free surgeries to\u00a0the world\u2019s neediest nations on the world\u2019s largest civilian hospital ship.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"http://www.nde.ong\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18805\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Mercy-Ship-Espana.png?resize=600%2C278\" alt=\"Mercy Ship Espana\" width=\"600\" height=\"278\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Mercy-Ship-Espana.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Mercy-Ship-Espana.png?resize=300%2C139&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">10. Project 1948 Foundation\u00a0\u25cf\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.project1948.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\">project1948.ngo<br />\n</a>?\u00a0United States</h2>\n<p><strong>Mission:</strong> To foster peace among\u00a0 young adults through the arts in post-war\u00a0Bosnia-Herzegovina.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.project1948.ngo\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18807\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Project-1948.png?resize=600%2C267\" alt=\"Project 1948\" width=\"600\" height=\"267\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Project-1948.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Project-1948.png?resize=300%2C134&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">11. Water for All\u00a0\u25cf\u00a0<a href=\"http://water4all.ngo\" target=\"_blank\">water4all.ngo<br />\n</a>?\u00a0Germany</h2>\n<p><strong>Mission:</strong> To\u00a0<span class=\"goog-text-highlight\">improve the water supply of the\u00a0</span>1.2 billion people worldwide who do not have clean drinking water.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.water4all.ngo\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18809\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Water-for-All.png?resize=600%2C289\" alt=\"Water for All\" width=\"600\" height=\"289\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Water-for-All.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/Water-for-All.png?resize=300%2C145&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">12. World Vision International\u00a0\u25cf\u00a0<a href=\"http://www.wvi.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\">wvi.ngo<br />\n</a>?\u00a0United Kingdom</h2>\n<p><strong>Mission: </strong>To\u00a0provide\u00a0sustainable transformation in the lives of poor children and provide emergency relief\u00a0that assists people afflicted by conflict or disaster.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.wvi.ngo/\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-18811\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/World-Vision-International.png?resize=600%2C299\" alt=\"World Vision International\" width=\"600\" height=\"299\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/World-Vision-International.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/12/World-Vision-International.png?resize=300%2C150&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 17px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;\"><em>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</em></span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\" target=\"_blank\"><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-16024\" style=\"margin: 10px; border: 1px solid black;\" src=\" http://www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/mobile-for-good-with-ribbon.jpg\" alt=\"mobile for good look inside\" width=\"99\" height=\"150\" /></a>Based on more than 20 years of experience and 25,000+ hours spent utilizing mobile and social media, <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\" target=\"_blank\"><em><strong>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</strong></em></a> is a comprehensive 256-page book packed with more than 500 best practices. Written on the premise that all communications and fundraising are now mobile and social, Mobile for Good is a step-by-step how-to guide for writing, implementing, and maintaining a mobile and social fundraising strategy for your nonprofit.</p>\n",
      "protected": false
    },
